title - Calculator

.section :split, "Splitting Strings", 58
  %p
    Splitting strings is one of the most common operation you will need to perform on String objects. Just like String#length, the method for split is String#split. If you split the String on space ' ', you can get an array of words within the given String. Let's try that:


   !enchant 64
      short_name :string_split_simple
      exercise!
      starting_code <<-DATA
             class Calculator
               def add
                 2
               end
             end
      DATA

      code_wrapper <<-DATA
         <%= user_code %>
      DATA

      specs <<-DATA
         it "is truthful" do
           Calculator.new.add(2,3).should eq(5)
         end
      DATA

   !release
